sentences: Since 2015 Guthrie Govan has been undertaking more frequently solo tours, mostly in Asia where he has a lot of fans requesting him to perform live.
In October 2012, Govan was seen using a Charvel guitar on tour, it was later confirmed to be a (koa) prototype.
Govan stated in January 2013 that he and Suhr parted ways officially.
In July 2013, Charvel made it official that they had joined forces with Govan, who had been using their guitars for a few months.

In January 2014 at the NAMM Show, Charvel officially introduced the Charvel USA Guthrie Govan Signature Model in two versions: one with a Birdseye Maple top and the other with a Flame Maple top, both equipped with custom pickups.
In 2017 Charvel added a newer lighter baked Ash body signature model to the GG-signature models and upgraded the former models with a single coil-humbucker switch.
Since 2013, Govan has started using amplifiers designed and produced by Victory Amplification for both Steven Wilson and the Aristocrats tours.
Since 2013, Guthrie has been taking his carry-on V30 across the globe.
Govan has been an analog fan concerning pedals, but for a few years (since 2016) he has been moving towards using a Fractal FX-8 live on tours.
Guthrie uses D'Addario guitar strings (NYXL 10-46) since October 2018.
